The '''Alliance Starbird''', also known as '''the Phoenix''', was a symbol of the [[Alliance to Restore the Republic/Legends|Alliance to Restore the Republic]]. It adorned the [[Flight helmet/Legends|flight helmets]] of a number of [[Rebel pilot/Legends|pilots]] during the [[Galactic Civil War/Legends|Galactic Civil War]] and represented the dream for the [[Galactic Republic/Legends|Galactic Republic]] to [[New Republic/Legends|rise again]].

==History==
[[File:Marek_Symbol_of_Hope.jpg|thumb|left|140px|The Rebel Alliance honoured Galen Marek by using the insignia.]]
By some accounts, the Alliance Starbird had been taken from the seal of the [[Galactic Republic/Legends|Old Republic]].<ref name="Heir to the Empire Sourcebook">''[[Heir to the Empire Sourcebook]]''</ref> And indeed, a similar winged seal had been used by the Republic at the time of the [[Great Galactic War]].<ref name="Timeline 1">{{TORweb|url=holonet/galactic-history|text=Timeline 1: Treaty of Coruscant|int=Timeline 1: Treaty of Coruscant}}</ref> However, the [[Alliance to Restore the Republic/Legends|Alliance to Restore the Republic]] adopted the symbol from the family crest of the [[House of Marek|Marek family]] in honor of [[Galen Marek]], Darth Vader's former apprentice, who sacrificed himself protecting the founders of the Alliance.<ref name="Star Wars: The Force Unleashed novelization">[[Star Wars: The Force Unleashed (novelization)|''Star Wars: The Force Unleashed'' novelization]]</ref> 

Often described as a rising phoenix, the Starbird represented the Alliance's goal of setting the stage for the Galactic Republic to rise again from the ashes of the [[Galactic Empire/Legends|Galactic Empire]] that it swore to topple. The Starbird most often appeared in bright red or blue but was also sometimes displayed in yellow, black, or gray.

When the Alliance became the [[New Republic/Legends|New Republic]], the Starbird was retained as the central image of the [[Insignia of the New Republic|new government's insignia]].<ref name="Heir to the Empire Sourcebook" />
[[Adar Tallon/Legends|Adar Tallon's]] family crest resembled an altered Starbird symbol.<ref name="Tatooine Manhunt">''[[Tatooine Manhunt]]''</ref>

Ultimately this symbol was used for a variety of different governments, including the Alliance to Restore the Republic,<ref name="ANH">{{Film|IV}}</ref> the [[Alliance of Free Planets]],<ref name="TABSB">''[[The Truce at Bakura Sourcebook]]''</ref> and the New Republic.<ref name="Heir to the Empire Sourcebook" /> A modified version existed that was used by the [[Galactic Federation of Free Alliances]], the [[Alliance-in-exile]], and over a century after Marek's death, the [[Galactic Alliance Remnant]] and the [[Galactic Federation Triumvirate]]. What's more, the Starbird was similar to the emblem of the [[Jedi Order/Legends|Old Jedi Order]], if somewhat modified, and later it became the symbol of the [[New Jedi Order]] and then of the temporary [[Jedi Coalition]].

==Behind the scenes==
A panel in [[Republic 78|''Republic'' 78]] shows a dark Starbird painted on the bow of a [[Dreadnaught-class heavy cruiser/Legends|''Dreadnaught''-class heavy cruiser]].<ref name="Star Wars Republic 78: Loyalties">[[Republic 78|''Republic'' 78]]</ref> This might indicate either that the Starbird was in use by the Republic during its late days, or that the vessel was serving under the auspices of the Marek family.

